\c 2
\s1 Not with human wisdom but with God's power
\m 
\v 1 \w So|strong="G4314"\w* \w when|strong="G2064"\w* \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, brothers, \w I|strong="G2504"\w* \w did|strong="G2316"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w proclaiming|strong="G2605"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w testimony|strong="G3142"\w*\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Instead of “testimony”, less than 5% of the Greek manuscripts have ‘mystery’, to be followed by the eclectic Greek text currently in vogue (as in some versions).\f* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w with|strong="G4314"\w* \w a|strong="G2064"\w* ‘\w superior|strong="G5247"\w*’ \w speech|strong="G3056"\w* \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w wisdom|strong="G4678"\w*.
